Context:
WAVE is a group of clinics where students provide health and wellness services to the public, with student rates applying to most services. The Daphne Cockwell Centre for Health Sciences at the Waterfront Campus provides access to technology and workplike environments for students preparing for healthcare careers.

Students in the School of Dental Health work in the George Brown College dental clinic and have field placements at clinics and dental offices throughout the Greater Toronto Area. Students in the School of Health and Wellness have hands-on learning experiences in diverse environments, such as specialized labs and fitness centres.

Students at the Sally Horsfall Eaton School of Nursing can pursue certificate, diploma, and degree programs that prepare them for careers in teaching, research, health care administration, and sales. They will study in the state-of-the-art Daphne Cockwell Centre for Health Sciences at the Waterfront Campus.

Contact information: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca.

The text mentions field placements in clinical settings including private practices, hospitals, and agencies for students in the School of Health Services Management. Students work with health information specialists on real client records (both electronic and paper) applying their academic learning about privacy and medical terminology in a practical, clinical setting.
